		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Macro's and Bards<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Macro's and Bards";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jul 31st 9:13 AM2002 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=102812119425558&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=102812119425558&post=1&replyto=102812119425558"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=117525"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=102812119425558></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=117525"><span id=>Master Solase</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />34 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Solase&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Okay, I've been playing for sometime now, but since the macro ability has been available, I have not used it, but I'm interested in how you might have setup your macros (i.e. cast 1, pause 30, etc.. ) .&nbsp;&nbsp;Please post if you know how to create a macro that will fit in at least 3 to 4 songs in one macro (not sure if it's possible, but would really like to know).<br><br> Sol<br> 56 Bard<br> Erollisi Marr</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Sol<br>58 Bard (Retired)<br>65 Feral Lord (Retired)<br>Maelin Starpyre</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Jul 31st 2:56 PM2002 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=102812119425558&post=1&replyto=102814098015909"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=102814098015909></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=60483"><span id=Scholar>Polyflame</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br />19 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Polyflame&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Heres what my bard has for macros:<br><br>Slot 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;Special Attack.  Basicly this macro makes you attack, and do 3 other commands at once.  This is a good macro for just about any melee class.<br>/attack off (Stops your attack)<br>/doability 1 (That would be something like beg or sense heading)<br>/doability 2 (That would be something else like doability 1)<br>/doability 7 (That would be Instill doubt, or change it to doability 3 if you want a normal skill.)<br>/attack on (Makes you attack)<br><br>Slot 2:  General slot 1.  It's just an empty slot in your inventory with no bag or anything on it.<br><br>Slot 3:  General slot 2.  This is another inventory slot, but with an instrument like drums or strings.<br><br>Slot 4:  General slot 3.  Same as slot 2.<br><br>Slot 5:  Primary melee slot.  Its your primary weapon slot.<br><br>Slot 6:  Secondary melee slot.  Its your secondary weapon slot.<br><br>Slot 7:  Song macro.  This is pretty cool, it lets you twist a bunch of songs with the click of a button.<br>/stopsong (Stops your current song)<br>/cast 1 (Casts your first song, best if a melee song)<br>/pause 30 (Pauses for 3 seconds)<br>/stopsong (You know what it does by now)<br>/cast 2 (Plays your second song)<br><br>Slot 8:  The second song macro.  This finishes off your song macros, and lets you twist 4 at once with ease.<br>/stopsong (Duh)<br>/cast 3 (Duh again)<br>/pause 30 (I shouldnt have to do this)<br>/stopsong (Dum de dum...)<br>/cast 4 (Voila!)<br><br>Slot 9:  Whatever you want, preferably the Forage skill.<br><br>Slot 10:  Whatever you want again.<br><br>Aaaaand there you have it my musical friends, macros for a bard.  You can replace slot 9 or 10 with another instrument slot if you wish.<br><br>Hope this helps, good luckest to thou =).</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />~Sloree<br>Nameless server<br>Level 46 Human Monk</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
